m-corrections%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emixed%20results%3C%2Fa%3E).%20While%20executives%20and%20the%20managerial%20class%20are%20all%20in%20on%20AI%2C%20there's%20been%20less%20consideration%20for%20the%20people%20this%20new%20tech%20will%20actually%20affect.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20mundane%20tasks%20that%20have%20so%20far%20been%20targeted%20for%20replacement%20are%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.com%2Fworklife%2Farticle%2F20230111-the-companies-that-churn-through-young-workers%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Egenerally%20handled%20by%20entry-level%20workers%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Managers%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-gen-z-is-changing-work-most-pro-labor-generation-2022-11%5C%22%3Egive%20these%20tasks%20to%20new%20hires%3C%2Fa%3E%20with%20the%20expectation%20that%20they'd%20be%20done%20quickly%2C%20done%20right%2C%20and%20done%20without%20anyone%20needing%20to%20really%20explain%20how%20to%20do%20them.%20This%20work%20was%20portrayed%20as%20a%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.com%2Fworklife%2Farticle%2F20211025-should-young-workers-still-have-to-pay-their-dues%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecritical%20part%20of%20their%20development%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20a%20way%20to%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.inc.com%2Fheather-r-huhman%2Feveryone-takes-entry-level-employees-for-granted-dont-make-that-mistake.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%26quot%3Bearn%20your%20stripes%26quot%3B%20in%20the%20workplace%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20tackling%20grunt%20work%20and%20hoping%20to%20learn%20a%20job%20via%20osmosis%20isn't%20a%20great%20way%20to%20start%20a%20career%2C%20corporate%20America%20has%20left%20young%20workers%20with%20few%20other%20options.%20Over%20the%20past%20several%20decades%2C%20many%20companies%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwheresyoured.at%2Fp%2Fthe-myth-of-mentorship-and-how-weve%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehave%20gutted%20training%20programs%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20neglected%20mentorship%2C%20and%20taken%20no%20responsibility%20for%20fostering%20workers'%20development.%20Now%2C%20with%20the%20advent%20of%20generative%20AI%2C%20organizations%20are%20starting%20to%20automate%20many%20%26quot%3Bjunior%26quot%3B%20tasks%20%E2%80%94%20stripping%20away%20their%20dubious%20last%20attempt%20to%20%26quot%3Bteach%26quot%3B%20young%20employees.%20It's%20no%20wonder%20that%20several%20surveys%20have%20found%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-an-opportunity-for-all-generations-even-gen-z-2023-6%5C%22%3Emembers%20of%20Gen%20Z%3C%2Fa%3E%20are%20particularly%20concerned%20about%20AI's%20effect%20on%20their%20careers%3B%20in%20a%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Faffiliate.insider.com%3Fh%3D844a8a431d225bb462442f588d29b198a15b0d02402b43aae6815bfa42e3c6e9%26postID%3D64ac3d5b30464171c2345a38%26site%3Dbi%26u%3Dhttps%253A%252F%252Fwww.ziprecruiter.com%252Fassets%252Fstatic%252Fpdf%252FJSCI%252FThe_ZipRecruiter_Confidence_Index_2023_Q1_3.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Erecent%20survey%20by%20the%20job-posting%20site%20ZipRecruiter%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%2076%25%20of%20Gen%20Zers%20indicated%20they%20were%20worried%20about%20losing%20their%20jobs%20to%20ChatGPT.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAmerica's%20young%20workers%20are%20headed%20toward%20a%20career%20calamity.%20They%20may%20be%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-ai-can-help-gen-z-succeed-workplace-2023-7%5C%22%3Emore%20comfortable%20using%20ChatGPT%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20other%20AI%20technology%20than%20their%20older%20coworkers%2C%20but%20the%20managerial%20obsession%20with%20artificial%20intelligence%20threatens%20to%20undermine%20their%20ability%20to%20launch%20a%20career.%20Management%20spent%20decades%20disconnecting%20themselves%20from%20the%20younger%20workers%20who%20are%20the%20backbone%20of%20their%20businesses.%20And%20if%20these%20executives%20already%20won't%20train%20their%20junior%20employees%2C%20it's%20no%20surprise%20they're%20ready%20to%20get%20rid%20of%20them%20altogether.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3ENobody%20wants%20to%20teach%20anymore%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EEven%20before%20the%20rise%20of%20AI%2C%20young%20people%20were%20facing%20an%20early-career%20crisis.%20Sure%2C%20on%20the%20surface%20it%20seems%20like%20Gen%20Z%20is%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgen-z-is-the-luckiest-generation-vs-millennials%5C%22%3Eentering%20the%20workforce%20at%20a%20great%20time%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Finding%20a%20job%20is%20much%20easier%20than%20it%20used%20to%20be%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Flabor-market-unemployment-rate-job-growth-june-report-2023-7%5C%22%3Ethanks%20to%20historically%20low%20unemployment%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20wages%20for%20young%20workers%20have%20been%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.epi.org%2Fblog%2Fclass-of-2023-young-workers-have-experienced-strong-wage-growth-since-2020%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Egrowing%20at%20a%20strong%20pace%3C%2Fa%3E.%20But%20if%20you%20look%20deeper%2C%20a%20growing%20number%20of%20signs%20suggest%20young%20Americans%20are%20going%20to%20have%20a%20much%20tougher%20time%20actually%20building%20a%20career.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGen%20Z%20is%20behind%20the%20eight%20ball%20even%20before%20their%20first%20day%20on%20the%20job.%20As%20the%20cost%20of%20college%20has%20soared%2C%20many%20of%20them%20are%20coming%20into%20their%20first%20job%20with%20a%20large%20student-debt%20burden.%20A%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.stlouisfed.org%2Fen%2Fon-the-economy%2F2022%2Faug%2Fhow-does-gen-z-student-debt-compare-millennials%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E2022%20study%20by%20the%20Federal%20Reserve%20Bank%20of%20St.%20Louis%3C%2Fa%3E%20found%20that%20Gen%20Zers%20were%20more%20likely%20than%20millennials%20were%20at%20their%20age%20to%20hold%20student%20debt%2C%20that%20Gen%20Zers'%20average%20debt%20load%20was%2013%25%20higher%20than%20millennials'%20was%2C%20and%20that%20roughly%20the%20same%20percentage%20of%20Gen%20Zers%20and%20millennials%20had%20%2450%2C000%20or%20more%20worth%20of%20outstanding%20student%20debt.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDon't%20want%20to%20go%20to%20college%3F%20Tough%20luck.%20Despite%20a%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wsj.com%2Farticles%2Femployers-rethink-need-for-college-degrees-in-tight-labor-market-11669432133%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Erecent%20pushback%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.vox.com%2Fpolicy%2F23628627%2Fdegree-inflation-college-bacheors-stars-labor-worker-paper-ceiling%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Enumber%20of%20jobs%20requiring%20a%20college%20degree%3C%2Fa%3E%20has%20been%20growing%20for%20decades.%20Even%20searching%20for%20a%20first%20job%20can%20leave%20Gen%20Zers%20scratching%20their%20heads.%20A%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Faffiliate.insider.com%3Fh%3D1757442d728c75fdc913147e9fd896b1631085132d8b7510e3a103140463829d%26postID%3D64ac3d5b30464171c2345a38%26site%3Dbi%26u%3Dhttps%253A%252F%252Fwww.linkedin.com%252Fnews%252Fstory%252Fnewbies-cant-get-entry-level-jobs-5117860%252F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ELinkedIn%20analysis%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%203.8%20million%20job%20postings%20from%202017%20to%202021%20found%20that%2035%25%20of%20entry-level%20jobs%20required%20at%20least%20three%20years%20of%20experience.%20And%20if%20you%20try%20to%20go%20the%20internship%20route%20to%20get%20that%20experience%3F%20Good%20luck.%20A%202021%20survey%20by%20the%20National%20Association%20of%20Colleges%20and%20Employers%20suggested%20that%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cnbc.com%2F2021%2F08%2F17%2Fmore-than-40percent-of-interns-are-still-unpaidwhy-thats-legal.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eover%2040%25%20of%20internships%20were%20unpaid%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20that%20the%20average%20hourly%20wage%20for%20paid%20interns%20was%20just%20%2420.76%20in%202020%20%E2%80%94%20a%20tight%20budget%20in%20many%20major%20metropolitan%20areas.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOnce%20young%20workers%20do%20finally%20break%20into%20the%20corporate%20world%2C%20they%20face%20another%20brutal%20reality%3A%20Companies%20have%20no%20interest%20in%20helping%20them%20move%20up%20the%20career%20ladder.%20Many%20companies%20have%20shown%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwheresyoured.at%2Fp%2Fthe-myth-of-mentorship-and-how-weve%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eabsolutely%20no%20consideration%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fjournals.sagepub.com%2Fdoi%2Fabs%2F10.1177%2F0019793915619904%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efostering%20and%20developing%20workers'%20abilities%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20leaving%20young%20workers%20to%20largely%20fend%20for%20themselves%20as%20they%20attempt%20to%20establish%20a%20career%20path.%20A%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nber.org%2Fpapers%2Fw20382%3Futm_campaign%3Dntw%26utm_medium%3Demail%26utm_source%3Dntw%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E2014%20study%20by%20Peter%20Cappelli%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20professor%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Pennsylvania's%20Wharton%20School%20of%20Business%2C%20found%20that%20in%201979%20%26quot%3Byoung%20workers%20received%20on%20average%20about%202.5%20weeks%20of%20training%20per%20year%26quot%3B%20but%20that%20by%201995%20it%20had%20fallen%20to%20just%20under%2011%20hours%20annually.%20Capelli%20also%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.washingtonpost.com%2Fnews%2Fon-leadership%2Fwp%2F2014%2F09%2F05%2Fwhat-employers-really-want-workers-they-dont-have-to-train%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efound%20scant%20evidence%20that%20things%3C%2Fa%3E%20had%20improved%20in%20the%20years%20since.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cblockquote%3E%3Cq%3ENow%2C%20with%20the%20advent%20of%20generative%20AI%2C%20organizations%20are%20starting%20to%20automate%20many%20%26quot%3Bjunior%26quot%3B%20tasks%20%E2%80%94%20stripping%20away%20their%20dubious%20last%20attempt%20to%20%26quot%3Bteach%26quot%3B%20young%20employees.%3C%2Fq%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdol.gov%2Fsites%2Fdolgov%2Ffiles%2FOASP%2Flegacy%2Ffiles%2Fjdt.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EThe%20US%20Department%20of%20Labor%20found%20in%202014%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20while%2070%25%20of%20firms%20offered%20%26quot%3Bsome%20type%20of%20training%20to%20employees%2C%26quot%3B%20it%20was%20mainly%20for%20%26quot%3Bmanagement%20and%20mid-level%20workers.%26quot%3B%20This%20statistic%20is%20particularly%20worrying%2C%20partly%20because%20%26quot%3Bsome%20type%20of%20training%26quot%3B%20is%20extremely%20vague%20and%20could%20refer%20to%20something%20as%20simple%20as%20reading%20the%20HR%20handbook%2C%20and%20partly%20because%2030%25%20of%20firms%20%3Cem%3Edidn't%20offer%20any%20training%20at%20all.%20%3C%2Fem%3EMore%20recently%2C%20in%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmitsloan.mit.edu%2Fideas-made-to-matter%2Fsurvey-workers-who-need-training-most-arent-getting-it%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ea%20survey%20conducted%20in%202020%20by%20Paul%20Osterman%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20professor%20at%20MIT%2C%20slightly%20less%20than%2050%25%20of%20employees%20said%20they'd%20received%20no%20formal%20job%20training%20from%20their%20employer%20over%20the%20past%20year.%20Osterman%20also%20argued%20in%20a%20discussion%20of%20the%20survey%20that%20companies%20were%20failing%20to%20provide%20employees%20with%20the%20types%20of%20training%20that%20would%20help%20boost%20their%20skills%20or%20advance%20their%20careers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYou%20might%20assume%20organizations%20would%20try%20to%20foster%20mentorship%20in%20the%20workforce%20as%20a%20way%20to%20make%20up%20for%20the%20lack%20of%20rigorous%20training.%20Not%20so%20fast.%20While%20mentorship%20is%20associated%20with%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov%2Fpmc%2Farticles%2FPMC2855142%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehigher%20levels%20of%20job%20satisfaction%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20organizational%20commitment%2C%20a%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.pewresearch.org%2Fsocial-trends%2F2023%2F03%2F30%2Fhow-americans-view-their-jobs%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E2023%20Pew%20Research%20Center%20survey%3C%2Fa%3E%20found%20that%20only%2044%25%20of%20Americans%20workers%20had%20one.%20And%20while%20formal%20mentorship%20programs%20exist%2C%20they're%20often%20voluntary.%20A%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nber.org%2Fpapers%2Fw29148%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Estudy%20from%20the%20National%20Bureau%20of%20Economic%20Research%3C%2Fa%3E%20found%20that%20voluntary%20mentorship%20programs%20led%20to%20worse%20outcomes%20than%20mandatory%20ones%20and%20that%20those%20who%20most%20needed%20the%20help%20of%20a%20mentor%20were%20less%20likely%20to%20join%20these%20types%20of%20programs.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20may%20be%20because%20workplace%20cultures%20often%20alienate%20those%20who%20ask%20for%20help%20(%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.seasons.com%2Fresearch-asking-for-help-benefits%2F2632464%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edespite%20the%20benefits%20of%20doing%20so%3C%2Fa%3E)%2C%20creating%20a%20pervasive%20feeling%20that%20organizations%20don't%20really%20care%20about%20their%20employees.%20In%20a%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.gallup.com%2F394424%2Findicator-employee-wellbeing.aspx%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eregular%20Gallup%20poll%20of%20US%20workers%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20only%2024%25%20of%20workers%20surveyed%20this%20May%20strongly%20agreed%20that%20their%20organizations%20cared%20about%20their%20well-being%2C%20down%20from%2033%25%20in%20May%202021%20and%20a%20remarkable%2049%25%20in%20May%202020.%20This%20lack%20of%20care%20is%20clearly%20weighing%20on%20the%20young%20workers%20who%20need%20career%20development%20the%20most.%20Workplace%20Intelligence%2C%20an%20HR-research%20firm%2C%20said%20that%20in%20a%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2Fworkplaceintelligence.com%2Fupskilling-study%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esurvey%20it%20conducted%20with%20Amazon%20in%202022%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%2074%25%20of%20Gen%20Zers%20and%20millennials%20indicated%20they%20were%20considering%20leaving%20their%20job%20%26quot%3Bdue%20to%20subpar%20skills-building%20support%20or%20a%20lack%20of%20career%20mobility%20options.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EWhy%20train%20when%20you%20can%20just%20plug%20it%20in%3F%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWith%20no%20training%20and%20no%20real%20professional%20development%2C%20young%20workers%20in%20recent%20years%20have%20been%20left%20with%20only%20one%20way%20to%20learn%20the%20ropes%20on%20the%20job%3A%20grunt%20work.%20In%20theory%2C%20these%20small%20jobs%20were%20meant%20to%20allow%20young%20workers%20to%20familiarize%20themselves%20with%20simpler%20processes%20and%20prove%20themselves%20competent%20enough%20to%20take%20on%20more%20challenging%20work.%20But%20they%20often%20resulted%20in%20young%20workers%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.npr.org%2F2023%2F01%2F25%2F1150816271%2Femployee-engagement-gallup-survey-workers-hybrid-remote%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efeeling%20a%20lack%20of%20purpose%20at%20work%3C%2Fa%3E%20because%20the%20work%20didn't%20feel%20like%20a%20meaningful%20contribution%20to%20the%20company%20or%20a%20way%20to%20actually%20progress%20to%20the%20next%20level.%20But%20with%20the%20advent%20of%20generative%20AI%20in%20the%20workplace%2C%20the%20jig%20is%20up.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cblockquote%3E%3Cq%3EYoung%20people%20will%20find%20themselves%20cleaning%20up%20the%20deluge%20of%20errors%20these%20faceless%20AI%20tools%20will%20spit%20out%2C%20knowing%20they'll%20receive%20less%20credit%20because%20the%20%26quot%3Bwork%26quot%3B%20came%20from%20a%20machine.%3C%2Fq%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%3Cp%3EAI%20has%20already%20begun%20to%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.washingtonpost.com%2Ftechnology%2F2023%2F06%2F02%2Fai-taking-jobs%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etake%20jobs%20from%20workers%20of%20all%20ages%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20but%20corporate%20America's%20particular%20disdain%20for%20its%20young%20means%20it%20will%20hit%20entry-level%20workers%20hardest.%20It%20takes%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-technology-chatgpt-silicon-valley-save-business-stock-market-jobs-2023-5%5C%22%3Ea%20lot%20of%20work%20to%20%26quot%3Btrain%26quot%3B%20a%20large%20language%20model%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20type%20of%20AI%20that%20powers%20ChatGPT%20and%20other%20similar%20products.%20But%20once%20that%20work%20is%20done%2C%20it's%20a%20lot%20cheaper%20for%20businesses%20to%20buy%20some%20new%20tech%20tools%20than%20train%20a%20real%20person%20%E2%80%94%20consequences%20be%20damned.%20For%20a%20managerial%20class%20that%20has%20all%20but%20rejected%20any%20responsibility%20for%20helping%20foster%20workers'%20growth%2C%20all%20that%20will%20matter%20is%20whether%20something%20is%20cheap%20and%20easy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20solace%20for%20these%20young%20workers%2C%20the%20managerial%20argument%20goes%2C%20is%20that%20the%20most%20tech-savvy%20among%20them%20will%20become%20the%20minders%20of%20these%20new%20machines.%20In%20reality%2C%20this%20means%20young%20people%20will%20find%20themselves%20cleaning%20up%20the%20deluge%20of%20errors%20these%20faceless%20AI%20tools%20will%20spit%20out%2C%20knowing%20they'll%20receive%20less%20credit%20because%20the%20%26quot%3Bwork%26quot%3B%20came%20from%20a%20machine.%20This%20has%20the%20potential%20to%20create%20a%20career%20crisis%20for%20young%20people%3A%20If%20even%20the%20faintest%20amount%20of%20freedom%20is%20wiped%20from%20their%20work%20lives%2C%20they'll%20have%20fewer%20ways%20to%20prove%20themselves%20capable%20of%20taking%20on%20more%20meaningful%20work.%20Promotions%20will%20become%20even%20more%20of%20a%20game%20of%20favorites%2C%20with%20the%20best%20%26quot%3Breal%26quot%3B%20tasks%20reserved%20for%20diplomats%20rather%20than%20hard%20workers.%20A%20new%20AI-powered%20model%20benefits%20established%20players%20and%20empowers%20America's%20weak%2C%20disconnected%20management%20culture%20that%20doesn't%20evaluate%20actual%20outputs%20or%20creations.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20no%20wonder%20CEOs%20and%20higher-ups%20are%20much%20more%20enthusiastic%20about%20integrating%20AI%20into%20the%20workplace%20than%20average%20employees%20are.%20The%20data%20company%20Qualtrics%20said%20that%20in%20a%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businesswire.com%2Fnews%2Fhome%2F20230613882872%2Fen%2FAI-Generates-Excitement-and-Fear-as-Employees-Worry-about-Job-Security%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esurvey%20it%20conducted%20in%20May%20and%20June%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%2064%25%20of%20executives%20suggested%20they%20found%20the%20%26quot%3Bpotential%20impact%20of%20AI%26quot%3B%20on%20their%20workplace%20exciting.%20Only%2039%25%20of%20frontline%20workers%20said%20the%20same%2C%20with%2046%25%20describing%20the%20tech%20as%20%26quot%3Bscary.%26quot%3B%20Another%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bcg.com%2Fpublications%2F2023%2Fwhat-people-are-saying-about-ai-at-work%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esurvey%20from%20Boston%20Consulting%20Group%3C%2Fa%3E%20registered%20a%20similar%20divide%3A%2062%25%20of%20execs%20and%20leaders%20were%20enthused%20about%20the%20prospect%20of%20using%20AI%20at%20work%2C%20compared%20with%2042%25%20of%20frontline%20employees.%20While%20AI%20optimists%20may%20predict%20that%20jobs%20we%20can't%20imagine%20right%20now%20will%20exist%20in%2010%20years%2C%20it's%20hard%20to%20imagine%2C%20given%20the%20ways%20corporations%20have%20deployed%20new%20technology%2C%20that%20automation%20will%20lead%20to%20a%20society%20where%20more%20people%20have%20more%20economic%20opportunities.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3ETrain%20the%20children%20%E2%80%94%20they're%20our%20only%20hope%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWhat's%20left%20for%20America's%20young%20workforce%3F%20What%20does%20a%20young%20person%20do%20in%20an%20office%20where%20they're%20not%20trained%2C%20mentored%2C%20or%20given%20%26quot%3Breal%26quot%3B%20work%3F%20What%20happens%20when%20early-career%20jobs%20like%20data%20entry%20and%20document%20filing%20are%20automated%20by%20artificial%20intelligence%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20irony%20is%20that%20corporate%20responsibility%20for%20employees%20is%20actually%20better%20for%20the%20business.%20Studies%20suggest%20that%20companies%20that%20invest%20in%20job%20training%20and%20skill%20development%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fresearch.upjohn.org%2Fcgi%2Fviewcontent.cgi%3Farticle%3D1053%26context%3Dup_press%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eare%20more%20efficient%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.shrm.org%2Fhr-today%2Fnews%2Fhr-magazine%2Fpages%2F0101wells.aspx%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ereap%20higher%20profit%20margins%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Despite%20this%20evidence%2C%20companies%20have%20a%20hard%20time%20grasping%20the%20value%20of%20the%20investment%20in%20their%20employees.%20As%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ffortune.com%2Fauthor%2Fulrich-atz%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EU%3C%2Fa%3Elrich%20Atz%20and%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ffortune.com%2Fauthor%2Ftensie-whelan%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ETensie%20W%3C%2Fa%3Ehelan%20from%20New%20York%20University's%20Stern%20Center%20for%20Sustainable%20Business%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ffortune.com%2F2023%2F05%2F10%2Fcompanies-human-capital-labor-cost-hurting-profits-shirtage-jobs-finance-atz-whelan%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ewrote%20recently%20in%20Fortune%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20corporations%20often%20don't%20have%20methods%20to%20measure%20the%20value%20of%20human%20capital%20beyond%20simple%20labor%20costs%2C%20meaning%20organizations%20consider%20humans%20in%20the%20same%20way%20they%20might%20consider%20the%20cost%20of%20their%20water%20or%20electric%20bills.%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwheresyoured.at%2Fp%2Fthe-rot-economy%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAmerica's%20rot%20economy%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20one%20where%2C%20to%20quote%20Atz%20and%20Whelan%2C%20%26quot%3Bcompanies%20are%20pressured%20to%20reduce%20costs%20in%20order%20to%20return%20more%20money%20to%20shareholders%26quot%3B%20%E2%80%94%20sees%20immediate%20revenue%20growth%20as%20the%20only%20valuable%20metric%20to%20consider%2C%20more%20important%20than%20the%20long-term%20value%20of%20growing%20an%20employee.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere's%20a%20better%20way%20to%20work%2C%20but%20I%20fear%20the%20only%20way%20for%20companies%20to%20learn%20the%20dangers%20of%20automation%20will%20be%20through%20a%20painful%20public%20example%20of%20a%20company%20that%20relied%20too%20much%20on%20AI%2C%20like%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Farchive.nytimes.com%2Fdealbook.nytimes.com%2F2012%2F08%2F02%2Fknight-capital-says-trading-mishap-cost-it-440-million%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EKnight%20Capital's%20trading%20glitch%20that%20cost%20it%20%24440%20million%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Humans%20can%20be%20enhanced%20by%20AI%2C%20helped%20by%20AI%2C%20but%20replacing%20them%20with%20AI%20is%20a%20shortsighted%20decision%20made%20by%20myopic%20bean%20counters%20who%2