e%20offences%20of%20money%20laundering%20and%20violations%20of%20foreign%20exchange%20laws.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20an%20editorial%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fmedia%2Fsuprem-court-enforcement-directorate-sk-mishra-amit-shah-editorials%5C%22%3Ethe%20%3Cem%3EDeccan%3C%2Fem%3E%20%3Cem%3EHerald%3C%2Fem%3E%20had%20highlighted%3C%2Fa%3E%20Shah%E2%80%99s%20odd%20defence%20of%20the%20ED%2C%20and%20noted%20that%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20ED%20is%20a%20statutory%20body%20with%20functions%20that%20it%20is%20expected%20to%20carry%20out%20without%20regard%20to%20the%20wishes%20of%20those%20in%20government.%20A%20member%20of%20the%20government%20has%20no%20reason%20or%20authority%20to%20speak%20on%20its%20behalf.%20The%20Home%20Minister%2C%20especially%2C%20has%20no%20reason%20to%20do%20so%20because%20the%20ED%20is%20attached%20to%20the%20Finance%20Ministry%2C%20not%20the%20Home%20Ministry.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1689580267000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F17131935%2FScreenshot-2023-07-17-at-1.19.22-PM.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Ftamil-nadu-enforcement-directorate-ponmudy%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Ponmudy%20is%20the%20second%20Tamil%20Nadu%20cabinet%20minister%20to%20be%20targeted%20by%20the%20central%20investigation%20agency.%20The%20searches%20come%20on%20a%20day%20when%2024%20opposition%20parties%20have%20united%20in%20Bengaluru%20to%20discuss%20a%20strategy%20to%20take%20on%20BJP%20in%202024.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Ftamil-nadu-enforcement-directorate-ponmudy%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22HDFC%20Bank%20Q1FY24%20results%3A%20Net%20profit%20jumps%2030%25%20to%20Rs%2011%2C952%20crore%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1689579774000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fbsmedia.business-standard.com%2F_media%2Fbs%2Fimg%2Farticle%2F2022-12%2F19%2Ffull%2F1671419641-0933.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Fcompanies%2Fresults%2Fhdfc-bank-q1fy24-results-net-profit-jumps-30-to-rs-11-952-crore-123071700329_1.html%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20bank's%20gross%20non-performing%20assets%20(GNPAs)%20rose%20slightly%20to%201.17%20per%20cent%20in%20Q1FY24%20as%20compared%20to%201.12%20per%20cent%20in%20Q4FY23%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A6%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Fcompanies%2Fresults%2Fhdfc-bank-q1fy24-results-net-profit-jumps-30-to-rs-11-952-crore-123071700329_1.html%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-business--standard-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Famp%2Fcompanies%2Fresults%2Fhdfc-bank-q1fy24-results-net-profit-jumps-30-to-rs-11-952-crore-123071700329_1.html%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Famp%2Fcompanies%2Fresults%2Fhdfc-bank-q1fy24-results-net-profit-jumps-30-to-rs-11-952-crore-123071700329_1.html%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22India's%20Frequent%20Internet%20Shutdowns%20Discussed%20at%20G20%20Meeting%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2021%2F01%2F07131244%2F2807100863_6b4b73964f_o.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EIndia%E2%80%99s%20frequent%20internet%20shutdowns%20came%20up%20for%20discussion%20at%20the%20recent%20G20%20meet%20on%20cybersecurity%2C%20with%20panelist%20Nneena%20Nwakanma%20saying%20that%20India%20should%20%E2%80%9Cstop%20shutting%20down%20the%20internet%20anytime%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENwakanma%2C%20associated%20with%20Geneva-based%C2%A0International%20Digital%20Health%C2%A0and%C2%A0AI%20Research%20Collaborative%2C%20was%20part%20of%20a%20panel%20discussion%20on%20%E2%80%98Internet%20Governance-National%20Responsibility%20and%20Global%20Commons%E2%80%99.%20%E2%80%9CI%20haven%E2%80%99t%20seen%20any%20case%20of%C2%A0internet%20shutdowns%20being%20taken%20to%20Parliament%2C%20nor%20is%20there%20any%20empirical%20evidence%20of%20economic%20returns%20(by%20imposing%20bans).%20Still%2C%20if%20law%20enforcement%20agencies%20need%20to%20impose%20a%20ban%2C%20they%20must%20follow%20the%20due%20process%20of%20law%20and%20elected%20representatives%20should%20be%20able%20to%20explain%20to%20their%20voters%20the%20reasons%20for%20such%20bans.%20Internet%20ban%20is%20one%20of%20the%20greatest%20dangers%20in%20building%20trust%20among%20the%20public%2C%E2%80%9D%20Nwakanma%20said%2C%20according%20to%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Feconomictimes.indiatimes.com%2Fnews%2Findia%2Fprimacy-of-right-to-life-says-india-at-g20-talks-on-internet-shutdowns%2Farticleshow%2F101805891.cms%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EEconomic%20Times%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIndia%20has%20the%20dubious%20distinction%20of%20being%20the%20internet%20shutdown%20capital%20of%20the%20world.%20As%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Ftech%2Findia-remains-internet-shutdown-capital-of-the-world-for-fifth-year-running-report%5C%22%3Eresearch%20by%20Access%20Now%20has%20shown%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20since%202016%2C%20India%20has%20accounted%20for%20approximately%2058%25%20of%20all%20shutdowns%20documented%20in%20the%20Shutdown%20Tracker%20Optimization%20Project%20(STOP%20database).%20India%20is%20the%20only%20G20%20country%20that%20has%20imposed%20an%20internet%20shutdown%20more%20than%20twice.%20Russia%20and%20Brazil%20are%20the%20other%20two%20courtiers%20that%20enforced%20two%20and%20one%20internet%20shutdowns%20respectively%20in%202022.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMost%20recently%2C%20in%20Manipur%20the%20government%20has%20indefinitely%20suspended%20internet%20services%20after%20ethnic%20violence%20broke%20out%20on%20May%203.%20The%20Supreme%20Court%20is%20hearing%20pleas%20against%20this%20suspension.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EResponding%20to%20a%20query%20on%20the%20frequent%20internet%20bans%20in%20India%2C%20former%20Intelligence%20Bureau%20chief%20and%20member%20of%20National%20Human%20Rights%20Commission%20Rajiv%20Jain%20reportedly%20stated%20that%20the%20right%20to%20life%20is%20sometimes%20in%20conflict%20with%20the%20right%20to%20freedom%20of%20expression%20and%20right%20to%20privacy.%20%E2%80%9CWhen%20there%20is%20a%20threat%20to%20life%20of%20a%20large%20group%20of%20people%20or%20in%20a%20large%20geographical%20area%2C%20primacy%20has%20to%20be%20given%20to%20Right%20to%20Life%20as%20the%20state%20acts%20as%20repository%20of%20all%20the%20rights%20and%20takes%20a%20call%20on%20temporary%20suspension%20of%20Internet%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said%2C%20according%20to%20%3Cem%3EEconomic%20Times%3C%2Fem%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1689579653000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2021%2F01%2F07131244%2F2807100863_6b4b73964f_o.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Findias-frequent-internet-shutdowns-discussed-at-g20-meeting%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Responding%20to%20a%20query%20on%20the%20frequent%20internet%20bans%20in%20India%2C%20former%20Intelligence%20Bureau%20chief%20and%20member%20of%20National%20Human%20Rights%20Commission%20Rajiv%20Jain%20reportedly%20stated%20that%20the%20right%20to%20life%20is%20sometimes%20in%20conflict%20with%20the%20right%20to%20freedom%20of%20expression%20and%20right%20to%20privacy.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Findias-frequent-internet-shutdowns-discussed-at-g20-meeting%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Kajol%20and%20Ajay%20spend%20'sacred%20time'%20with%20Nysa%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1689579264000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-101819263%2Cimgsize-38600.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fentertainment%2Fhin