w%2F101812284.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20border%3D%5C%220%5C%22%20align%3D%5C%22left%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fphoto%2F101812284.cms%5C%22%20hspace%3D%5C%2210%5C%22%3E%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A7%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Feurope%2Ftraffic-stopped-on-crimean-bridge-reports-of-blasts%2Farticleshow%2F101812284.cms%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fm-timesofindia-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fm.timesofindia.com%2Fworld%2Feurope%2Ftraffic-stopped-on-crimean-bridge-reports-of-blasts%2Famp_articleshow%2F101812284.cms%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fm.timesofindia.com%2Fworld%2Feurope%2Ftraffic-stopped-on-crimean-bridge-reports-of-blasts%2Famp_articleshow%2F101812284.cms%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Restoring%20Democracy%3A%20An%2011-Point%20Common%20Minimum%20Programme%20for%20the%20United%20Opposition%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F17081051%2FIMG_2494-1.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWhen%20the%20Janata%20coalition%20won%20the%201977%20elections%2C%20following%20the%20Emergency%2C%20its%20path%20to%20undo%20at%20least%20the%20more%20obvious%20damage%20inflicted%20on%20Indian%20democracy%20by%20Indira%20Gandhi%20was%20clear.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EGandhi%20had%20introduced%20most%20of%20her%20formal%20full-frontal%20assaults%20on%20democracy%20through%20the%2042%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3End%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%20Amendment%20to%20the%20Constitution%2C%20and%20the%20Janata%20government%20enacted%20the%2044%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Eth%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%20Amendment%20to%20roll%20back%20most%20of%20what%20she%20had%20done.%20If%20the%20united%20opposition%20wins%20the%202024%20%E2%80%93%20or%2C%20if%20rumours%20are%20to%20be%20believed%2C%20the%202023%20%E2%80%93%20general%20elections%20against%20the%20odds%2C%20it%20won%E2%80%99t%20have%20the%20luck%20of%20the%20Janata%20government%3B%20for%20the%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.degruyter.com%2Fdocument%2Fdoi%2F10.1515%2Flehr-2020-2009%2Fhtml%3Flang%3Den%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Ecrimes%20of%20the%20Modi%20regime%20against%20the%20Constitution%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20have%20been%20subtle%2C%20informal%2C%20incremental%2C%20and%20numerous.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThere%20is%20simply%20no%20clear%20object%20like%20the%2042%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3End%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%20Amendment%20to%20target.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWhat%20is%20more%2C%20mere%20restoration%20will%20not%20suffice%20if%20the%20opposition%20really%20cares%20about%20Indian%20democracy.%20Many%20of%20the%20excesses%20of%20the%20Modi%20regime%20have%20taken%20advantage%20of%20existing%20fault-lines%20in%20our%20constitutional%20framework%20%E2%80%93%20weaknesses%20that%20most%20previous%20governments%20have%20also%20been%20guilty%20of%20weaponising%2C%20albeit%20not%20to%20the%20same%20extent%20and%20not%20with%20the%20same%20degree%20of%20constitutional%20shamelessness%20as%20the%20Modi%20regime.%20If%20the%20opposition%20victory%20is%20to%20mark%20a%20never-again%20moment%2C%20the%20new%20government%20cannot%20stop%20at%20restoration.%20It%20has%20to%20formulate%20an%20agenda%20not%20only%20for%20restoration%2C%20but%20also%20for%20democratic%20deepening%20and%20entrenchment.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EMuch%20of%20this%20democratic%20entrenchment%20agenda%20requires%20the%20recognition%20and%20empowerment%20of%20the%20political%20opposition%20as%20a%20legitimate%20part%20of%20the%20state%2C%20representing%20a%20significant%20proportion%20of%20the%20population.%20It%20requires%20an%20acknowledgement%20that%20in%20our%20constitutional%20scheme%2C%20the%20ruling%20party%2Fcoalition%20is%20only%20meant%20to%20dominate%20the%20higher%20executive%20and%20the%20lower%20house%20of%20the%20legislature%2C%20and%20only%20for%20a%20fixed%20period%20of%20time.%20Although%20these%20institutions%20of%20government%20hold%20the%20reins%20of%20state%20power%2C%20the%20state%20is%20bigger%20than%20the%20government%2C%20and%20includes%20judges%2C%20guarantor%20institutions%2C%20the%20bureaucracy%2C%20and%20the%20elected%20legislators%20of%20the%20political%20opposition%20as%20legitimate%20public%20officers.%20It%20will%20be%20tempting%20for%20the%20opposition%20parties%20%E2%80%93%20who%20have%20faced%20the%20undeserved%20wrath%20of%20a%20petty%20and%20brutal%20regime%20%E2%80%93%20to%20want%20to%20exact%20revenge%20by%20paying%20back%20in%20kind.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20idea%20of%20rewarding%20a%20Bharatiya%20Janata%20Party%20in%20opposition%20by%20entrenching%20opposition%20rights%20and%20powers%20could%20be%20truly%20galling%20to%20normal%20human%20instincts.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EBut%20it%20is%20essential%20that%20they%20understand%20opposition%20empowerment%20not%20as%20rewarding%20the%20BJP%2C%20but%20rather%20as%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Facademic.oup.com%2Ficon%2Farticle%2F15%2F4%2F988%2F4872580%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Ebuying%20political%20insurance%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20for%20their%20future%20selves%2C%20whenever%20it%20is%20their%20turn%20to%20be%20once%20again%20in%20opposition.%20The%20long-term%20success%20of%20Indian%20democracy%20rests%20on%20the%20acknowledgement%20that%20democracy%20is%20a%20system%20in%20which%20parties%20lose%20power%2C%20and%20that%20the%20opposition%20is%20part%20of%20the%20state%20even%20as%20it%20sits%20outside%20of%20the%20government.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EFinally%2C%20the%20united%20opposition%20must%20remember%20that%20%E2%80%93%20like%20the%20Janata%20government%20%E2%80%93%20a%20non-BJP-coalition%20government%20in%202024%20that%20includes%20parties%20as%20diverse%20as%20the%20Shiv%20Sena%2C%20Aam%20Aadmi%20Party%2C%20and%20the%20Left%20(many%20of%20whom%20are%20the%20main%20political%20rivals%20of%20the%20Congress%20in%20the%20states)%20%E2%80%93%20will%20likely%20be%20unstable.%20Such%20a%20government%20will%20therefore%20have%20but%20a%20short%20period%20of%20time%20to%20justify%20its%20formation%2C%20and%20should%20act%20in%20a%20manner%20that%20would%20obviate%20the%20need%20for%20such%20diverse%20ideological%20bedfellows%20to%20have%20to%20come%20together%20ever%20again%20merely%20to%20ensure%20the%20survival%20of%20our%20democracy%20(on%20which%20their%20own%20survival%20of%20course%20depends).%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ETherefore%2C%20here%20is%20a%20list%20of%20things%20that%20should%20be%20seriously%20considered%20by%20the%20united%20opposition%20in%20its%20Common%20Minimum%20Programme%20to%20restore%20and%20entrench%20Indian%20democracy.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ciframe%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fflo.uri.sh%2Fvisualisation%2F14460856%2Fembed%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22Interactive%20or%20visual%20content%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%20data-mce-type%3D%5C%22bookmark%5C%22%3E%EF%BB%BF%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3E1.%20Electoral%20System%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EPerhaps%20the%20single%20most%20important%20thing%20a%20non-BJP%20government%20could%20do%20to%20entrench%20Indian%20democracy%20and%20also%20minority%20rights%20is%20to%20abolish%20the%20first-past-the-post%20system%20in%20favour%20of%20Australian-style%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findianexpress.com%2Farticle%2Fopinion%2Fcolumns%2Fgeneral-elections-lok-sabha-polls-first-past-the-post-fpp-system-bjp-5715812%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eranked-choice%20voting%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20(RCV)%20for%20Lok%20Sabha%20and%20Vidhan%20Sabha%20elections.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20290px)%2085vw%2C%20290px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F17085516%2FWhatsApp-Image-2023-07-17-at-7.51.16-AM.jpeg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22290%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F17085516%2FWhatsApp-Image-2023-07-17-at-7.51.16-AM.jpeg%20795w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F17085516%2FWhatsApp-Image-2023-07-17-at-7.51.16-AM-233x300.jpeg%20233w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-663506%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22374%5C%22%3EThe%20new%20system%20would%20expand%20voter%20choice%20by%20giving%20people%20the%20option%20of%20ranking%20their%20top%20two%20or%20three%20candidates%20in%20order%20of%20preference%2C%20rather%20than%20simply%20endorsing%20a%20single%20candidate%20as%20currently%20happens.%20RCV%20system%20employs%20exactly%20the%20same%20process%20as%20the%20single-transferable%20vote%20(STV)%20the%20Constitution%20already%20employs%20for%20Rajya%20Sabha%20elections%20%E2%80%93%20the%20main%20difference%20being%20that%20STV%20is%20used%20when%20multiple%20candidates%20are%20to%20be%20elected%2C%20whereas%20the%20term%20RCV%20is%20typically%20reserved%20for%20elections%20in%20which%20there%20will%20be%20a%20single%20winner.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ECounting%20takes%20place%20over%20multiple%20rounds%2C%20such%20that%20the%20candidate%20with%20the%20least%20number%20of%20first-choice%20votes%20in%20each%20round%20is%20eliminated%2C%20and%20her%20second-ranked%20votes%20are%20then%20allocated%20to%20all%20remaining%20candidates.%20The%20rounds%20of%20counting%20continue%20until%20one%20candidate%20crosses%20a%2050%25%20threshold%20or%20is%20the%20last%20candidate%20standing%2C%20once%20all%20others%20have%20been%20eliminated.%20Under%20RCV%2C%20the%20winning%20candidate%20has%20a%20greater%20democratic%20legitimacy%20than%20the%20current%20system%20where%20one%20can%20win%20even%20after%20garnering%20a%20mere%2035%25%20or%20so%20votes%2C%20as%20long%20as%20the%20opposition%20votes%20are%20divided.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAlso%2C%20because%20divisive%20parties%20like%20the%20BJP%20are%20typically%20either%20a%20voter%E2%80%99s%20first%20choice%20or%20last%20choice%2C%20RCV%20forces%20parties%20to%20build%20a%20big%20enough%20tent%20to%20accommodate%20voters%20who%20may%20not%20have%20opted%20for%20them%20as%20their%20first%20choice%20but%20who%20are%20willing%20to%20tolerate%20them%20as%20their%20secondary%20preference.%20Furthermore%2C%20ideologically%20cognate%20parties%20end%20up%20transferring%20their%20votes%20to%20each%20other%2C%20rather%20than%20under-cutting%20each%20other%2C%20thereby%20better%20approximating%20voters%E2%80%99s%20ideological%20preferences.%20This%20simple%20change%20could%20not%20only%20enhance%20our%20quality%20of%20democracy%20but%20also%20push%20our%20politics%20towards%20the%20centre%20ground%2C%20and%20away%20from%20the%20extremes%20where%20it%20presently%20teeters.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EContrast%20this%20centripetal%20effect%20with%20the%20much-touted%20proportional%20representation%2C%20which%20incentivises%20smaller%20parties%20to%20become%20extremists%20in%20order%20to%20distinguish%20themselves%20from%20centrist%20parties%2C%20and%20can%20sometimes%20hand%20the%20balance%20of%20power%20to%20such%20extremist%20parties%20(as%20recent%20experience%20in%20Israel%20instructively%20demonstrates).%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ERCV%20can%20be%20introduced%20by%20a%20simple%20statutory%20amendment%20to%20the%20Representation%20of%20the%20People%20Act%2C%20for%20the%20Constitution%20only%20requires%20territorial%20constituency-based%20direct%20elections%2C%20and%20is%20completely%20silent%20on%20whether%20this%20should%20be%20by%20first-past-the-post%20or%20ranked-choice%20vote.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3E2.%20Independent%20institutions%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAlongside%20this%20change%20in%20the%20electoral%20system%2C%20the%20new%20government%20will%20also%20need%20to%20quickly%20enact%20the%20Independent%20Institutions%20Bill.%20Such%20a%20Bill%20is%20a%20long-unfulfilled%20constitutional%20mandate%20that%20leaves%20it%20for%20parliament%20to%20specify%20a%20fair%20(and%2C%20therefore%2C%20multi-partisan)%20manner%20of%20appointments%20to%20constitutional%20institutions%20(like%20the%20higher%20judiciary%20and%20guarantor%20institutions%20like%20the%20Election%20Commission%2C%20the%20Auditor%20General%2C%20governors%20and%20so%20on)%2C%20as%20well%20as%20to%20quasi-constitutional%20bodies%20like%20the%20Information%20Commission%20that%20were%20set%20up%20by%20statute.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20main%20way%20to%20secure%20this%20is%20to%20ensure%20that%20the%20political%20opposition%20is%20given%20an%20equal%20say%20in%20the%20appointment%20process%20alongside%20the%20ruling%20party.%20I%20recommended%20one%20way%20of%20realising%20this%20mandate%20in%20this%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findianexpress.com%2Farticle%2Fopinion%2Fcolumns%2Findependent-institutions-bill-opposition-holding-up-fourth-branch-5629032%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eprior%20column%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Einvolving%20a%20two-stage%20appointments%20process%20comprising%20multi-partisan%20shortlisting%20committees%20in%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%20or%20Vidhan%20Sabha%20(to%20draw%20up%20a%20shortlist%20of%20applicants%2Fnominees%20based%20on%20STV)%20and%20a%20multi-partisan%20appointments%20committee%20of%20the%20Rajya%20Sabha%20(which%20finalises%20the%20appointee%2C%20also%20through%20preferential%20vote).%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3E3.%20Judicial%20independence%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAllied%20changes%20to%20ensure%20the%20separation%20of%20the%20state%20and%20the%20government%2C%20and%20their%20separation%20from%20the%20ruling%20party%2C%20include%20the%20raising%20of%20the%20retirement%20age%20of%20Supreme%20Court%20and%20high%20court%20judges%20to%20at%20least%2068%20years%20(which%20will%20reduce%20the%20appeal%20of%20post-retirement%20office%20somewhat)%2C%20and%20the%20introduction%20of%20a%20cooling-off%20period%20of%20at%20least%20one%20year%20after%20retirement%20for%20any%20other%20public%20posts%20for%20judges.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EFurthermore%2C%20we%20need%20a%20provision%20for%20ensuring%20that%20any%20post-retirement%20appointments%20can%20only%20be%20made%20by%20the%20multi-partisan%20mechanism%20in%20the%20new%20Independent%20Institutions%20Bill%20or%20an%20independent%20judicial%20appointments%20commission%2C%20and%20not%20by%20the%20government%20of%20the%20day.%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3E4.%20Opposition%20rights%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Office%20of%20the%20Leader%20of%20opposition%20must%20be%20recognised%20as%20the%20leader%20of%20the%20government-in-waiting%20through%20a%20constitutional%20amendment%2C%20and%20every%20legislative%20house%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3Emust%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3Ehave%20a%20leader%20of%20the%20opposition%20elected%20through%20ranked-choice-vote%20by%20all%20opposition%20legislators%20(in%20a%20vote%20administered%20by%20the%20Election%20Commission).%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Leader%20of%20Opposition%20must%20have%3A%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3Ea)%20the%20right%20of%20audience%20with%20the%20president%2Fgovernor%2C%20the%20prime%20minister%2Fchief%20minister%2C%20the%20senior%20civil%20service%2C%20the%20military%2C%20the%20intelligence%20agencies%2C%20and%20members%20of%20all%20constitutional%20and%20quasi-constitutional%20institutions%20(except%20the%20judiciary)%2C%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3Eb)%20the%20right%20to%20be%20briefed%20regularly%20on%20all%20matters%20of%20national%20security%2C%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3Ec)%20the%20right%20to%20receive%20copies%20of%20any%20draft%20Bills%20the%20government%20proposes%20to%20introduce%20in%20any%20House%20at%20least%2024%20hours%20before%20such%20introduction%2C%20and%20the%20right%20to%20be%20consulted%20on%20any%20draft%20Ordinance%20proposed%20by%20the%20government%20with%20at%20least%2048%20hours%20notice%20to%20record%20objections%20or%20amendments%2C%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3Ed)%20the%20right%20to%20convene%20sessions%20of%20the%20legislative%20house%20(without%20needing%20governmental%20approval)%20and%20the%20right%20to%20set%20the%20agenda%20and%20timetable%20for%20one%20day%20of%20every%20legislative%20week%20(%E2%80%98opposition%20day%E2%80%99)%2C%20in%20consultation%20with%20all%20opposition%20parties%2C%20and%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3Ee)%20the%20standing%20to%20bring%20any%20constitutional%20challenge%20before%20high%20courts%20or%20the%20Supreme%20Court%2C%20which%20the%20courts%20may%20refuse%20to%20admit%20only%20after%20giving%20detailed%20written%20reasons.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3E5.%20Equality%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%20Given%20the%20Modi%20regime%E2%80%99s%20treatment%20of%20all%20manner%20of%20minorities%20as%20second%20class%20citizens%2C%20the%20new%20government%20will%20also%20need%20to%20quickly%20enact%20a%20comprehensive%2C%20multi-sector%2C%20multi-ground%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findianexpress.com%2Farticle%2Fopinion%2Fcolumns%2Fshashi-tharoor-introduces-ade-anti-discrimination-equality-bill-4584252%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eanti-discrimination%20law%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20that%20applies%20to%20the%20public%20and%20the%20private%20sector.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIndia%20remains%20one%20of%20the%20very%20few%20democracies%20still%20without%20such%20a%20law%2C%20despite%20the%20UN%20recently%20recognising%20that%20its%20member-states%20are%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ohchr.org%2Fen%2Fpublications%2Fpolicy-and-methodological-publications%2Fprotecting-minority-rights-practical-guide%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eobliged%20under%20international%20law%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20to%20enact%20it.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EDiscriminatory%20laws%20and%20policies%2C%20such%20as%20the%20Citizenship%20Amendment%20Act%2C%20the%20National%20Register%20of%20Citizenship%2C%20the%20so-called%20%E2%80%98love%20jihad%E2%80%99%20laws%2C%20the%20anti-conversion%20laws%2C%20the%20segregationist%20%E2%80%98disturbed%20areas%E2%80%99%20acts%2C%20the%20SC%2FST%20exclusion%20in%20the%20Economically%20Weaker%20Sections%20quota%2C%20etc.%20will%20need%20to%20be%20repealed.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EA%20consultative%2C%20genuinely%20egalitarian%2C%20uniform%20civil%20code%20based%20on%20the%20opt-in%20model%20of%20the%20Special%20Marriage%20Act%20may%20also%20be%20considered.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3E6.%20Federalism%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20damage%20to%20India%E2%80%99s%20federal%20structure%20needs%20to%20be%20repaired.%20Governors%20must%20be%20appointed%20for%20non-renewable%20fixed-terms%20on%20the%20recommendation%20of%20a%20two-stage%20multi-partisan%20mechanism.%20Confidence%20chambers%20of%20legislatures%20could%20be%20mandated%20to%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3Edirectly%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20elect%20a%20chief%20minister%2Fprime%20minister%20through%20run-off%20elections%20in%20the%20House%2C%20without%20the%20intervention%20of%20the%20governor%20or%20president.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EBasically%2C%20soon%20after%20the%20elections%20for%20a%20House%2C%20the%20three%20largest%20parties%20should%20have%20the%20right%20to%20nominate%20any%20member%20of%20the%20House%20as%20a%20candidate%20and%20all%20elected%20legislators%20can%20vote%20to%20indicate%20their%20preferred%20choice%20for%20the%20post.%20If%20one%20candidate%20crosses%20the%2050%25%20threshold%2C%20they%20become%20the%20PM%2FCM.%20If%20not%2C%20the%20top-two%20candidates%20from%20the%20first%20round%20of%20voting%20run%20against%20each%20other%20in%20a%20second%20round%20of%20votes%20by%20the%20legislators%2C%20and%20the%20winner%20gets%20elected%20as%20the%20PM%2FCM.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThis%20system%20completely%20eliminates%20the%20discretion%20of%20the%20Governor%2FPresident%20to%20prefer%20a%20particular%20leader%20to%20form%20a%20government%20and%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3Ethen%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3Eseek%20the%20confidence%20of%20the%20House.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EFurthermore%2C%20the%20principle%20of%20asymmetric%20federalism%20under%20India%E2%80%99s%20Constitution%20needs%20to%20be%20reasserted%20and%20strengthened%20as%20a%20key%20feature%20of%20our%20unity%20in%20diversity%2C%20especially%20in%20relation%20to%20states%20outside%20the%20politically%20dominant%20%E2%80%98mainland%E2%80%99%2C%20such%20as%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir%20and%20the%20Northeastern%20states.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3E7.%20State%20capture%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20role%20of%20money%20in%20politics%20needs%20serious%20attention%20too.%20The%20electoral%20bonds%20scheme%20needs%20urgent%20repeal%2C%20and%20all%20foreign%20funding%20for%20political%20parties%20must%20be%20prohibited%20%E2%80%93%20it%20is%20astonishing%20that%20the%20BJP%20government%20has%20allowed%20so%20much%20foreign%20and%20corporate%20control%20of%20our%20politics.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20State%20Capture%20Commission%20%E2%80%93%20along%20the%20lines%20of%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.statecapture.org.za%2F%5C%22%3EZondo%20Commission%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20South%20Africa%20%E2%80%93%20to%20investigate%20the%20alleged%20capture%20of%20state%20institutions%20and%20public%20assets%20by%20a%20handful%20of%20crony%20capitalists%20in%20cahoots%20with%20the%20ruling%20party%2C%20needs%20to%20be%20established%20to%20allocate%20accountability%20and%20to%20recommend%20measures%20to%20protect%20against%20state%20capture.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3E8.%20Anti-defection%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20use%20of%20money%20to%20break%20up%20opposition%20parties%20needs%20to%20stop%20too%20%E2%80%93%20it%20requires%20strengthening%20anti-defection%20laws%20through%20a%20constitutional%20amendment%2C%20such%20that%20a%20candidate%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3Eautomatically%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20loses%20their%20legislative%20seat%20if%20they%20reject%20their%20party%20leadership%E2%80%99s%20whip%20on%20a%20confidence%20vote%20or%20a%20finance%20bill.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ESuch%20a%20move%20will%20need%20to%20be%20balanced%20against%20the%20freedom%20of%20expression%20of%20legislators%20by%20removing%20the%20threat%20of%20anti-defection%20law%20on%20all%20other%20matters%20of%20legislative%20business%2C%20whereby%20defiance%20of%20the%20party%20whip%20can%20only%20be%20dealt%20with%20by%20internal%20party%20discipline%2C%20and%20does%20not%20result%20in%20loss%20of%20one%E2%80%99s%20seat.%20Needless%20to%20say%2C%20any%20such%20move%20will%20also%20require%20clear%20rules%20to%20determine%20who%20leads%20the%20legislative%20party%3A%20one%20such%20method%20being%20to%20require%20each%20party%E2%80%99s%20elected%20legislators%20to%20elect%20the%20leader%20of%20the%20legislative%20party%2C%20administered%20by%20the%20Election%20Commission%20using%20ranked-choice-vote%20(to%20ensure%20the%20winner%20has%20the%20support%20of%20more%20than%2050%25%20legislators).%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWritten%20requests%20to%20the%20Election%20Commission%20by%20a%20fixed%20percentage%20of%20the%20membership%20of%20the%20legislative%20party%20%E2%80%93%20say%2030%25%20%E2%80%93%20should%20be%20able%20to%20trigger%20a%20fresh%20leadership%20election.%20Such%20a%20system%20would%20do%20away%20with%20the%20concept%20of%20a%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3Esplit%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20in%20the%20party%3A%20a%20legislative%20party%20always%20remains%20intact%20under%20one%20leader%2C%20democratically%20elected.%20If%20the%20dissenting%20members%20are%20unhappy%20with%20the%20elected%20leader%2C%20nothing%20prevents%20them%20from%20resigning%20their%20seats%2C%20thereby%20triggering%20a%20by-election%20and%20running%20under%20the%20banner%20of%20a%20new%20or%20different%20party.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThis%20is%20but%20one%20option%20that%20needs%20to%20be%20considered%3A%20how%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3EOperation%20Black%20Lotus%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%20is%20genuinely%20decommissioned%20would%20clearly%20require%20a%20serious%20constitutional%20debate.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E9.%20Lawfare%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20last%20nine%20years%20have%20seen%20numerous%20allegations%20that%20public%20officers%20have%20weaponised%20the%20law%20against%20political%20dissenters%2C%20including%20journalists%2C%20activists%2C%20academics%2C%20protestors%2C%20and%20politicians.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20Truth%20%26amp%3B%20Justice%20Commission%2C%20aided%20by%20a%20special%20investigative%20team%2C%20should%20be%20established%20to%20prosecute%20all%20such%20crimes%20by%20public%20servants.%20Some%20mitigation%20in%20sentencing%20should%20be%20allowed%20for%20officers%20who%20come%20forward%20to%20make%20full%20and%20truthful%20public%20confessions.%20Whistle-blowers%20should%20be%20protected%20and%20rewarded.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20manner%20in%20which%20the%20officialdom%20has%20victimised%20dissenters%20must%20never%20be%20permitted%20again%2C%20and%20ensuring%20this%20requires%20the%20political%20courage%20to%20bring%20to%20book%20all%20corrupt%20officers%20who%20violated%20fundamental%20rights%20at%20the%20behest%20of%20their%20political%20patrons%20or%20politicians%20who%20ordered%20such%20violations.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3E10.%20Civil%20liberties%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20criminal%20justice%20system%20needs%20a%20complete%20overhaul.%20All%20procedural%20shortcuts%20and%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thehindu.com%2Fopinion%2Fop-ed%2FDealing-with-issues-of-impunity%2Farticle15134034.ece%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eimpunity%20provisions%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20that%20shield%20public%20officers%20in%20laws%20such%20as%20Armed%20Forces%20(Special%20Powers)%20Act%2C%20Unlawful%20Activities%20(Prevention)%20Act%2C%20National%20Investigation%20Agency%2C%20etc.%20will%20need%20to%20go.%20So%20too%20will%20colonial-era%20crimes%20like%20sedition%2C%20criminal%20defamation%20and%20so%20on.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ELaws%20suppressing%20freedom%20of%20association%20and%20speech%2C%20such%20as%20the%20FCRA%2C%20and%20unnecessary%20procedural%20hurdles%20to%20assemble%20for%20protest%2C%20also%20need%20to%20be%20reformed.%20Genuine%20professionalisation%20and%20departisanisation%20of%20the%20police%20forces%2C%20intelligence%20agencies%20and%20prosecutorial%20offices%20is%20long%20overdue.%C2%A0%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20high-level%20Commission%20for%20the%20Democratisation%20of%20the%20Criminal%20Justice%20System%20to%20recommend%20measures%20to%20give%20civil%20liberties%20the%20respect%20they%20deserve%20in%20a%20democracy%20would%20need%20to%20be%20constituted.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3E11.%20Knowledge%20institutions%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFinally%2C%20a%20Commission%20on%20Media%20Freedom%20and%20Academic%20Freedom%20should%20look%20into%20the%20capture%20of%20or%20aggressive%20lawfare%20against%20truth-telling%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cjccl.ca%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2021%2F05%2F7-Jackson.pdf%5C%22%3Eknowledge%20institutions%3C%2Fa%3E%20like%20the%20media%20and%20the%20universities.%20The%20power%20of%20the%20government%20to%20fund%20advertisements%20in%20media%20clearly%20needs%20to%20be%20checked.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELaws%20ensuring%20media%20pluralism%20%E2%80%93%20such%20as%20the%20Australian%20requirement%20of%20at%20least%20five%20different%20media%20outlets%20with%20distinct%20ownership%20and%20editorial%20controls%20%E2%80%93%20need%20to%20be%20given%20serious%20consideration.%20Requiring%20all%20news%20media%20outlets%20and%20universities%20to%20register%20as%20not-for-profit%20companies%20or%20charities%20is%20another%20reform%20necessary%20to%20protect%20these%20freedoms%20from%20corporate%20capture.%20Universities%20need%20to%20be%20released%20from%20the%20clutches%20of%20political%20masters%2C%20and%20the%20UGC%20needs%20to%20be%20reformed%20to%20remove%20the%20power%20of%20the%20government%20to%20direct%20its%20funding%20powers.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%C2%A7%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ENeedless%20to%20say%2C%20the%20list%20above%20is%20intended%20to%20spark%20a%20debate.%20It%20is%20not%20meant%20to%20be%20comprehensive%2C%20nor%20is%20it%20intended%20as%20a%20proposal%20of%20definitive%20plans.%20It%20leaves%20out%20major%20structural%20issues%20like%20political%20economy%2C%20gender%20justice%2C%20caste%20and%20other%20forms%20of%20inequality%2C%20which%20any%20government%20worth%20its%20salt%20should%20to%20attend%20to.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%2011%20proposals%20above%20are%20presented%20in%20a%20manner%20that%20most%20parties%20in%20the%20united%20opposition%20should%20be%20able%20to%20agree%20with%20%E2%80%93%20even%20though%2C%20on%20merits%2C%20I%20think%20the%20institution%20of%20governors%20and%20the%20power%20to%20issue%20ordinances%20merit%20complete%20abolition%2C%20rather%20than%20mere%20reform.%20The%20various%20Commissions%20I%20have%20proposed%20are%20necessary%20because%20the%20facts%20and%20the%20shape%20of%20required%20reforms%20are%20very%20unclear%20in%20the%20current%20context%2C%20even%20though%20readers%20would%20be%20forgiven%20their%20cynicism%20for%20commission-led%20solutions.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EStrong%20political%20will%20would%20be%20required%20to%20do%20even%20half%20of%20what%20is%20proposed.%20The%20main%20purpose%20of%20this%20list%20is%20to%20remind%20the%20united%20opposition%20that%20although%20the%20need%20to%20focus%20on%20winning%20the%20next%20general%20elections%20is%20difficult%20to%20overstate%2C%20winning%20is%20only%20the%20first%20step.%20It%20also%20needs%20to%20spare%20some%20intellectual%20and%20political%20capital%20for%20setting%20out%20to%20shape%20what%20its%20Common%20Minimum%20Programme%20might%20look%20like.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cspan%3ETarunabh%20Khaitan%20is%20the%20Head%20of%20Research%20at%20the%20Bonavero%20Institute%20of%20Human%20Rights%20(Oxford)%20and%20the%20Professor%20of%20Public%20Law%20%26amp%3B%20Legal%20Theory%20(Oxford).%20He%20is%20shortly%20due%20to%20take%20up%20the%20role%20of%20Professor%20(Chair)%20of%20Public%20Law%20at%20the%20London%20School%20of%20Economics%20and%20Political%20Science.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1689564235000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F17081051%2FIMG_2494-1.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Funited-opposition-democracy-common-minimum-programme%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22If%20an%20opposition%20victory%20is%20to%20mark%20a%20never-again%20moment%2C%20the%20new%20government%20cannot%20stop%20at%20restoration.%20It%20has%20to%20formulate%20an%20agenda%20not%20only%20for%20restoration%2C%20but%20also%20for%20democratic%20deepening%20and%20entrenchment.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A12%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Funited-opposition-democracy-common-minimum-programme%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%2217%20kanwariya%20deaths%20during%2012-day%20yatra%20in%20Haridwar%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1689563805000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%