2C%20a%20heavy%20cousin%20of%20hydrogen%2C%20and%20carbon-14%20are%20also%20sources%20produced%20when%20high-energy%20protons%20from%20space%20smash%20into%20oxygen%20and%20nitrogen%20atoms%20in%20the%20air.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20atmospheric%20source%20of%20ocean%20radioactivity%20has%20worked%20on%20Earth%20for%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nature.com%2Farticles%2Fs41561-020-0538-9%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Ealmost%20three%20billion%20years%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Along%20with%20uranium%20radioactive%20decay%20products%2C%20humans%20live%20within%20this%20natural%20radioactive%20background.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20year%20the%20Japanese%20government%20plans%20to%20release%201.3%20million%20tonnes%20of%20water%20%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%93%20%3C%2Fspan%3Eused%20to%20cool%20the%20damaged%20reactor%20cores%20from%20the%20Fukushima%20Daiichi%20Nuclear%20Power%20Plant%20accident%20in%20March%202011%20%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%93%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%20into%20the%20Pacific%20Ocean%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBetween%202011-2013%2C%20approximately%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fweb.archive.org%2Fweb%2F20110516154816%2Fhttp%3A%2Fwww.asahi.com%2Fenglish%2FTKY201105120189.html%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3E300%2C000%20tonnes%20of%20untreated%20wastewater%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0had%20already%20flowed%20into%20the%20ocean%20off%20Fukushima.%20These%20first%20two%20years%20were%20the%20most%20dangerous%20time%20because%20long-lived%20heavy%20nuclei%2C%20like%20cesium-137%2C%20strontium-90%20and%20shorter-lived%20iodine-131%2C%20from%20nuclear%20fission%20in%20the%20reactors%20ended%20up%20in%20the%20ocean.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESince%202013%2C%20the%20stored%20water%20has%20also%20accumulated%20flushed%20seawater%20goundwater%20which%20leaked%20into%20the%20three%20damaged%20reactor%20cores.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20big%20challenge%20is%20how%20to%20manage%201.3%20million%20tonnes%20of%20unsafe%20radioactively-tainted%20water.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOne%20of%20three%20options%20was%20to%20filter%20out%20the%20nuclear%20fission%20nuclei%2C%20then%20dump%20the%20filtered%20water%20into%20the%20ocean%20to%20dilute%20any%20remaining%20amount%20of%20tritium%20or%20carbon-14.%20%C2%A0Japan%20has%20chosen%20this%20complex%20way%20from%20all%20the%20fraught%20options.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDisposing%20of%20untreated%20wastewater%20into%20the%20ocean%20would%20release%20nuclear%20fission%20products%20in%20an%20uncontrolled%20manner.%20The%20danger%20of%20indiscriminately%20releasing%20nuclear%20fission%20products%20into%20the%20ocean%20is%20that%20the%20products%20can%20find%20their%20way%20into%20the%20food%20chain.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOnce%20in%20the%20food%20chain%2C%20the%20nuclear%20fission%20heavy%20nuclei%20like%20cesium-137%2C%20strontium-90%20and%20iodine-131%20tend%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.abc.net.au%2Fscience%2Farticles%2F2011%2F06%2F21%2F3245821.htm%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Econcentrate%20in%20human%20muscle%2C%20bones%2C%20and%20thyroid%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20cause%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2Fwww.bioline.org.br%2Fpdf%3Fja07057%5C%22%3ECancer%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20is%20why%20Japan%20planned%20to%20remove%20as%20much%20of%20these%20radioactive%20nuclei%20as%20possible%20from%20the%20Fukushima%20water%20before%20its%20release.%20Some%20cesium-137%20and%20strontium-90%20%C2%A0nuclei%20already%20exist%20on%20the%20ocean%20floor%20due%20to%20nuclear%20weapons%20tests%20in%20the%201950s%20and%2060s.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20good%20guide%20for%20having%20confidence%20in%20the%20safe%20release%20of%20radiation%20is%20to%20reduce%20human%20radiation%20exposure%20by%20making%20it%20%E2%80%9CAs%20Low%20As%20Reasonably%20Achievable%E2%80%9D%20or%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cdc.gov%2Fnceh%2Fradiation%2Falara.html%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3EALARA%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFiltering%20out%20the%20nuclear%20fission%20nuclei%20from%20the%20stored%20wastewater%20may%20be%20the%20best%20that%20can%20be%20done.The%20ALARA%20approach%20to%20reduce%20nuclear%20fission%20nuclei%20released%20resulted%20in%20a%202013%20effort%20to%20develop%20and%20employ%20an%20advanced%20liquid%20processing%20system%2C%20or%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.tepco.co.jp%2Fen%2Fnu%2Ffukushima-np%2Fhandouts%2F2013%2Fimages%2Fhandouts_130329_01-e.pdf%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3EALPS%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%20A%20series%20of%20filters%20was%20designed%20to%20remove%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.iaea.org%2Fsites%2Fdefault%2Ffiles%2Freport_1_review_mission_to_tepco_and_meti.pdf%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3E62%20fission%20nuclei%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0leaving%20both%20tritium%20and%20carbon-14%20in%20the%20water.%20%C2%A0It%20only%20partially%20worked.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Tokyo%20Electric%20Power%20company%20(TEPCO)%20and%20the%20International%20Atomic%20Energy%20Agency%20(IAEA)%20agree%20that%20about%2070%25%20of%20the%20stored%20Fukushima%20water%20may%20still%20carry%20some%20of%20the%20original%20nuclear%20fission%20nuclei.%20Potentially%2C%20this%20water%20could%20be%20run%20through%20more%20cycles%20of%20the%20ALPS%20before%20extra%20dilution%20and%20later%20release%20into%20the%20ocean.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20other%2030%25%20of%20treated%20water%20could%20also%20be%20diluted%20with%20seawater%20by%20factors%20of%20several%20hundred%20to%20one%20thousand%20and%20then%20released%20into%20the%20ocean.%20Any%20remaining%20tritium%20from%20the%20Fukushima%20reactor%20may%20find%20its%20way%20into%20the%20food%20chain%20as%20organically%20bound%20tritium%20via%20build-up%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.sciencedirect.com%2Fscience%2Farticle%2Fpii%2FS0025326X0100039X%3Fcasa_token%3DrU1zVGEdYYMAAAAA%3ArO5YwPfC1BWdCjRSA2hjh38Vm0LPcBd79Gg42kaVhE76hroYTnj7zEaLPRyiXmn32TGX4yqK%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Eunderwater%20plants%20and%20organisms%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOrganically%20bound%20tritium%20will%20still%20keep%20its%2012.4-year%20half-life%2C%20but%20these%20nuclei%20stay%20in%20the%20human%20body%20for%20roughly%2010%20days%20before%20half%20of%20their%20number%20is%20excreted.%20The%2010%20days%20is%20known%20as%20the%20biological%20half-life%20of%20tritium.%20The%20process%20for%20excreting%20carbon-14%20has%20a%20biological%20half-life%20of%20about%2040%20days%2C%20which%20is%20negligible%20compared%20to%20its%205%2C730-year%20radioactive%20decay%20half-life.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThese%20short%20biological%20half-lives%20contrast%20sharply%20with%20the%20decades-long%20residence%20time%20of%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.epa.gov%2Fradiation%2Fradionuclide-basics-cesium-137%23cesiumhealth%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Ecesium-137%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0and%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.epa.gov%2Fradiation%2Fradionuclide-basics-strontium-90%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Estrontium-90%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0inside%20the%20human%20body.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20second%20option%20for%20managing%20the%20Fukushima%20water%20was%20to%20hold%20it%20on%20site%20in%20an%20ever-increasing%20number%20of%20tanks.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIf%20the%20water%20is%20properly%20filtered%20to%20leave%20only%20tritium%20and%20carbon-14%2C%20then%20the%20natural%20decay%20of%20tritium%20can%20be%20used%20to%20reduce%20overall%20radioactivity.%20%C2%A0Since%20the%20radioactive%20half-life%20of%20tritium%20is%2012.4%20years%2C%20holding%20the%20water%20in%20tanks%20for%20seven%20half-lives%2C%20about%2085%20years%2C%20would%20reduce%20the%20tritium%20content%20to%20less%20than%201%25%20of%20its%20current%20value.%20This%20option%20leaves%20the%20carbon-14%20which%20would%20still%20roughly%20have%20the%20same%20radioactivity%20due%20to%20its%205%2C730-year%20half-life.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20storing%20a%20tremendous%20volume%20of%20water%20for%20an%20entire%20human%20lifespan%20has%20never%20been%20tried.%20Even%20more%20water%20and%20storage%20tanks%20would%20need%20to%20be%20added%20as%20decommissioning%20the%20Fukushima%20Daiichi%20nuclear%20reactor%20cores%20proceeds.%20This%20is%20problematic.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20third%20option%20was%20to%20evaporate%20the%20water%20on%20land%20near%20Fukushima.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%201979%20nuclear%20accident%20at%20Three%20Mile%20Island%20Nuclear%20Station%20in%20the%20United%20States%20resulted%20in%20a%20similar%20radioactive%20water%20storage%20problem.%20About%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcollections.digitalmaryland.org%2Fdigital%2Fapi%2Fcollection%2Fsaac%2Fid%2F42040%2Fdownload%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3E9%2C300%20tonnes%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0of%20tritiated%20water%2C%20about%20140%20times%20less%20than%20that%20currently%20held%20in%20the%20Fukushima%20storage%20tanks%2C%20was%20electrically%20evaporated%20over%20two%20years.%20The%20tritium%20was%20released%20into%20the%20atmosphere%2C%20resulting%20in%20a%20radiation%20dose%20to%20people%20in%20the%20surrounding%20area%20of%20about%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nrc.gov%2Freading-rm%2Fdoc-collections%2Ffact-sheets%2F3mile-isle.html%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Eone-hundredth%20of%20the%20natural%20background%20radiation.%C2%A0%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EJapan%20and%20TEPCO%20would%20need%20to%20deal%20with%20even%20larger%20amounts%20of%20water%20and%20tritium%20emitted%20into%20the%20atmosphere%20if%20the%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.iaea.org%2Fsites%2Fdefault%2Ffiles%2Freport_1_review_mission_to_tepco_and_meti.pdf%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3E30-year%20timeline%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0for%20the%20reactor%20core%20clean-up%20is%20followed.%20Again%2C%20this%20option%20was%20too%20problematic.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20crucial%20to%20distinguish%20natural%20background%20radiation%20from%20that%20of%20nuclear%20fission%20nuclei%20when%20seeking%20to%20understand%20the%20choice%20made%20by%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theguardian.com%2Fenvironment%2F2023%2Ffeb%2F15%2Ffukushima-japan-insists-release-of-treated-water-is-safe-nuclear-disaster%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3EJapan%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0and%20supported%20by%20the%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.iaea.org%2Ftopics%2Fresponse%2Ffukushima-daiichi-nuclear-accident%2Ffukushima-daiichi-alps-treated-water-discharge%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3EIAEA%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Nobody%20wants%20to%20add%20additional%20radiation%20to%20the%20oceans%2C%20if%20only%20because%20of%20sympathy%20with%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theguardian.com%2Fenvironment%2F2019%2Fsep%2F16%2Ffukushima-fisherman-fear-for-future-over-release-of-radioactive-water%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Elocal%20Fukushima%20fishers%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20with%20proper%20ALPS%20filtering%2C%20people%20who%20go%20out%20to%20swim%20in%20the%20ocean%20should%20still%20have%20radiation%20exposure%20as%20the%20least%20of%20their%20concerns.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3EDr%20David%20Krofcheck%20is%20a%20Senior%20Lecturer%20in%20Physics%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Auckland.%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20article%20was%20orginally%20published%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2F360info.org%2Fa-deep-dive-into-the-reality-of-radioactive-water%2F%5C%22%3E360News%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1689511169000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F16173220%2F3e08d767-76b2-473f-b4a9-c602b2f3a53e.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fenvironment%2Fjapan-to-release-1-3-million-tonnes-of-water-used-during-fukushima-nuclear-accident%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20water%20used%20to%20cool%20damaged%20reactor%20cores%20from%20the%20Fukushima%20Daiichi%20Nuclear%20Power%20Plant%20accident%20in%20March%202011.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A8%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fenvironment%2Fjapan-to-release-1-3-million-tonnes-of-water-used-during-fukushima-nuclear-accident%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22India%20Asks%20Myanmar%20to%20Avoid%20Actions%20That%20Aggravate%20Border%20Situation%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F16165045%2FF1IaVFRaMAAZEtQ.jpeg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20India%20has%20told%20Myanmar%20that%20the%20border%20areas%20have%20been%20%E2%80%9Cseriously%20disturbed%E2%80%9D%20and%20to%20avoid%20any%20actions%20that%20would%20%E2%80%9Caggravate%E2%80%9D%20the%20situation.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20was%20conveyed%20by%20external%20affairs%20minister%20S.%20Jaishankar%20during%20a%20rare%20bilateral%20discussion%20with%20Myanmar%E2%80%99s%20foreign%20minister%20U%20Than%20Swe%20in%20Bangkok%2C%20where%20both%20took%20part%20in%20a%20Mekong%20Ganga%20Cooperation%20meeting%20on%20Sunday.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2FDrSJaishankar%2Fstatus%2F1680434567633838080%3Fs%3D20%5C%22%3EIn%20a%20tweet%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Jaishankar%20said%20that%20he%20underlined%20the%20importance%20of%20ensuring%20peace%20and%20stability%20in%20our%20border%20areas.%20%E2%80%9CThese%20have%20been%20seriously%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.aljazeera.com%2Fnews%2F2023%2F1%2F25%2Fwarning-of-escalation-after-myanmar-air-raids-near-india-border%5C%22%3Edisturbed%3C%2Fa%3E%20recently%20and%20any%20actions%20that%20aggravate%20the%20situation%20should%20be%20avoided%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20wrote.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20January%20this%20year%2C%20the%20Ministry%20of%20External%20Affairs%20had%20taken%20up%20the%20issue%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.tribuneindia.com%2Fnews%2Fnation%2Fmyanmar-bomb-did-fall-in-india-but-no-air-space-violation-mea-471950%5C%22%3Eair%20strikes%3C%2Fa%3E%20by%20the%20Myanmar%20military%20against%20rebels%20after%20a%20bomb%20fell%20on%20the%20Indian%20side%20of%20the%20border.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Indian%20minister%20also%20stated%20that%20he%20%E2%80%9Cflagged%20concerns%20about%20human%20and%20drug%20trafficking%E2%80%9D%20and%20urged%20cooperation%20for%20the%20%E2%80%9Cearly%20return%20of%20trafficked%20victims%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIndia%20has%20a%201%2C643%20kilometre%20long%20border%20with%20Myanmar%20which%20runs%20along%20four%20states%20in%20the%20north%20east.%20Due%20to%20its%20proximity%20to%20India%E2%80%99s%20sensitive%20northeastern%20region%2C%20there%20have%20been%20concerns%20about%20the%20military%20junta%E2%80%99s%20actions%20which%20drive%20refugees%20across%20the%20border%2C%20as%20well%20as%20their%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fasiatimes.com%2F2021%2F12%2Fmyanmar-military-joining-hands-with-indian-rebels%2F%5C%22%3Einconsistent%3C%2Fa%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.news18.com%2Fnews%2Findia%2Fmyanmar-army-abandons-taga-headquarters-of-northeast-insurgent-groups-after-three-years-5450287.html%5C%22%3Eattitude%3C%2Fa%3E%20towards%20insurgent%20groups.%20Over%2050%2C000%20refugees%20are%20estimated%20to%20have%20fled%20across%20into%20India%20following%20the%20junta%E2%80%99s%20crackdown%20after%20the%202021%20coup.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EJaishankar%20also%20noted%20that%20India%20was%20%E2%80%9Cconcerned%20about%20the%20humanitarian%20situation%20in%20Myanmar%E2%80%9D%20and%20proposed%20%E2%80%9Cpeople-centric%20initiatives%20aimed%20to%20address%20the%20pressing%20challenges%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EJust%20like%20other%20neighbours%2C%20India%20has%20remained%20engaged%20with%20the%20military%20junta%20after%20the%20February%202021%20coup%2C%20though%20New%20Delhi%20has%20also%20raised%20the%20issue%20of%20democracy%20at%20all%20political%20encounters.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EJaishankar%20again%20stated%20that%20India%20%E2%80%9Csupports%20the%20democratic%20transition%20process%20in%20Myanmar%20and%20highlights%20the%20need%20for%20return%20of%20peace%20and%20stability%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20reiterated%20that%20India%20%E2%80%9Cclosely%20coordinates%20our%20policy%20with%20ASEAN%20in%20this%20regard%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EJaishankar%20was%20earlier%20in%20Indonesia%20where%20ASEAN%20foreign%20ministers%20re-endorsed%20the%20five-point%20consensus.%20However%2C%20the%20Myanmar%20foreign%20minister%20was%20barred%20from%20attending%20the%20conference%20as%20the%20junta%20had%20failed%20to%20meet%20its%20commitments%20under%20the%20consensus.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThailand%20deviated%20from%20the%20collective%20approach%20of%20ASEAN%20when%20its%20foreign%20minister%20Don%20Pramudwinai%2C%20visited%20Myanmar%20and%20met%20with%20the%20detained%20ousted%20leader%20Aung%20San%20Suu%20Kyi%2C%20who%20is%20currently%20held%20by%20the%20military%20junta.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIndia%20seems%20to%20be%20aligning%20with%20the%20Thai%20initiative%20to%20have%20a%20separate%20channel%20of%20engagement%20since%20the%20ASEAN%20method%20seems%20to%20have%20stalled.%20In%20June%2C%20India%20had%20taken%20part%20in%20a%20meeting%20hosted%20by%20Thailand%20of%20neighbouring%20countries%20and%20Myanmar%2C%20which%20had%20seen%20three%20major%20ASEAN%20countries%20rebuff%20the%20Thai%20invitation.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%20Jaishankar%20said%20that%20on%20the%20connectivity%20issue%2C%20India%20conveyed%20that%20it%20was%20important%20to%20expedite%20projects%20%E2%80%9Cthat%20have%20faced%20challenges%20in%20the%20recent%20past%2C%20especially%20the%20India-Myanmar-Thailand%20trilateral%20highway%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELater%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2FDrSJaishankar%2Fstatus%2F1680530471355031556%5C%22%3Eduring%20the%20MGC%20meeting%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Jaishankar%20again%20raised%20the%20issue%20implementing%20the%20much-delayed%20trilateral%20highway%20and%20also%20concluding%20the%20motor%20vehicle%20agreement%20between%20the%20three%20countries.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1689507952000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F16165045%2FF1IaVFRaMAAZEtQ.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fdiplomacy%2Findia-asks-myanmar-to-avoid-actions-that-aggravate-bo